<h2>General Local Search Behavior</h2>
<p>These 10 statistics show how consumers find local businesses through search.</p>
<p><strong>1. 46% of all Google searches have local intent.</strong>
Source: Search Engine Roundtable
Nearly half of every Google query seeks a local result. That is billions of searches per day with purchase intent baked in.</p>
<p><strong>2. 98% of consumers search online for nearby companies.</strong>
Source: BrightLocal, 2024
Only 2% of consumers skip online search entirely. A local business without online visibility is invisible to 98 out of 100 potential customers.</p>
<p><strong>3. 80% of U.S. consumers search for local businesses weekly.</strong>
Source: SOCi Consumer Behavior Index, 2024
Four out of 5 Americans run a local search every week. Weekly search frequency means weekly opportunities to <a href="/blog/how-to-rank-higher-google/">rank higher on Google</a>.</p>
<p><strong>4. 32% search for local businesses daily.</strong>
Source: SOCi, 2024
Nearly 1 in 3 consumers searches for a local business every day. Daily searchers represent the highest-intent buyers in your market.</p>
<p><strong>5. 87% of consumers use Google to find local businesses.</strong>
Source: Statista, 2024
Google dominates local discovery. No other platform comes close for local search volume.</p>
<p><strong>6. 1.5 billion "near me" searches happen every month.</strong>
Source: Synup, 2024
That is 50 million "near me" queries per day. Each one signals a consumer ready to visit, call, or buy.</p>
<p><strong>7. 900% increase in "near me" searches over the past 2 years.</strong>
Source: Google/Think with Google
"Near me" queries grew 9x in 24 months. This growth rate shows no signs of slowing through 2026.</p>
<p><strong>8. 72% of consumers who did a local search visited a store within 5 miles.</strong>
Source: HubSpot/Google
Local search drives foot traffic. Nearly 3 in 4 searchers end up at a physical location close to them.</p>
<p><strong>9. 62% of consumers would avoid a business with incorrect online information.</strong>
Source: BrightLocal, 2023
Wrong hours, old phone numbers, or a bad address cost you customers. Accurate <a href="/glossary/citation/">citations</a> are not optional.</p>
<p><strong>10. 42% of searchers click on results within the Google Map Pack.</strong>
Source: Backlinko, 2024
The <a href="/glossary/local-pack/">local pack</a> captures nearly half of all clicks. Ranking in those top 3 map results matters more than any other position.</p>
