Nearly every consumer reads reviews before choosing. A business without reviews is a business without social proof.</p>
<p><strong>20. 41% "always" read reviews before choosing a local business.</strong>
Source: BrightLocal LCRS, 2026
Up from 29% in 2025. The habit of checking reviews is becoming automatic for consumers.</p>
<p><strong>21. 68% will only use a business rated 4+ stars.</strong>
Source: BrightLocal LCRS, 2026
Up from 55% in 2025. The minimum star rating bar keeps climbing year over year.</p>
<p><strong>22. 31% require 4.5+ stars before considering a business.</strong>
Source: BrightLocal LCRS, 2026
Up from 17% in 2025. Nearly 1 in 3 consumers filters out anything below 4.5 stars.</p>
<p><strong>23. Consumers use an average of 6 different review sites.</strong>
Source: BrightLocal LCRS, 2026
Google is not the only place reviews matter. Consumers cross-reference Yelp, Facebook, industry directories, and more.</p>
<p><strong>24. 74% seek reviews from the last 3 months.</strong>
Source: BrightLocal LCRS, 2026
Old reviews lose their influence. Fresh reviews from the past 90 days carry the most weight.</p>
<p><strong>25. 80% more likely to use a business that responds to all reviews.</strong>
Source: BrightLocal LCRS, 2026
